Package de.bioforscher.singa.mathematics.topology

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    MetricSpace
    A metric space is a set for which distances between all members of the set are defined.
    TopologicalSpace
    A topological space may be defined as a set of points, along with a set of neighbourhoods for each point.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    EuclideanSpace
    The Euclidean space or plane is a set of points, that satisfy certain relationships, expressible in terms of distance and angle.
    SpaceProvider
    The SpaceProvider class has some often used spaces predefined.
